---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Details
description: a disclosure widget that shows and hides content
nhsuk: https://service-manual.nhs.uk/design-system/components/details
---

{% from "components/details/macro.njk" import details %}

<h2>Default (closed)</h2>
{{ details({
  summary: "Where can I find my NHS number?",
  html: "<p>Your NHS number is on any letter from the NHS, such as your
    medical card, prescriptions, or test results. If you cannot find it,
    your GP surgery can tell you your NHS number.</p>"
}) }}

<h2>Open by default</h2>
{{ details({
  summary: "What is an NHS number?",
  open: true,
  text: "It is a 10-digit number that uniquely identifies you in the NHS."
}) }}

<h2>With list content</h2>
{% call details({ summary: "When should I dial 999?" }) %}
<ul>
  <li>signs of a heart attack or stroke</li>
  <li>serious bleeding that will not stop</li>
  <li>severe difficulty breathing</li>
  <li>severe burns or scalds</li>
</ul>
{% endcall %}

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>The component uses the native <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> and
  <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> elements, which provide keyboard support
  (<kbd>Tab</kbd> to focus, <kbd>Enter</kbd> or <kbd>Space</kbd> to toggle)
  and expose the expanded/collapsed state to assistive tech for free.
  No JavaScript is required.</p>
